<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="12" pageNumber="167" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,565,755]" box="[212,320,565,588]" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
<heading box="[212,320,565,588]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="167" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,320,565,588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,565,755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
The only Patagonian species of 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[586,884,604,628]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Stilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Acanthohelea">
<emphasis box="[586,707,604,628]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Stilobezzia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[726,876,604,628]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Acanthohelea</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
that is large (male wing length 
<quantity box="[291,455,636,660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8899999999999997" metricValueMax="3.03" metricValueMin="2.75" pageId="12" pageNumber="167" unit="mm" value="2.8899999999999997" valueMax="3.03" valueMin="2.75">2.75–3.03 mm</quantity>
; female wing length 
<quantity box="[695,859,636,660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.59" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.38" pageId="12" pageNumber="167" unit="mm" value="2.59" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.38">2.38–2.80 mm</quantity>
), with the body completely covered with long, coarse setae and tarsomeres 1–2 of all legs bearing two apical spines. Males sternite 9 with a posteromedian hyaline projection and posterior margin of tergite 9 bilobate. Females scutellum with 10–12 large and 8–10 thinner setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,816,1606]" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis box="[212,421,817,841]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[291,406,817,841]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Head. Dark brown. Antennal flagellum brown; plume dark brown, poorly developed; antennal ratio 1.10–1.16 (1.13, 
<emphasis box="[761,774,849,872]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 2). Palpus dark brown; segment 3 cylindrical, slightly shorter than 1; palpal ratio 4.14–4.57 (4.35, 
<emphasis box="[926,939,881,904]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,816,1606]" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[354,507,912,936]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Figure 3C, D</figureCitation>
). Scutum dark brown except humeral pits, lateral margins, two sublateral longitudinal bands, prescutellar depression yellowish; scutellum yellowish with 28–30 large setae in two rows; postscutellum dark brown, narrow lateral margin yellowish; pleura yellowish brown, distal half of katepisternum dark brown, proximal half yellowish. Legs dark brown, with dense, coarse setae; apex of hind tibia slightly darker; hind femur, tibia greatly enlarged, femur swollen; tarsomeres 1–2 of all leg with two apical spines; tarsomere 1 of hind leg with ventral row of spines; hind tibial comb with 11 spines; prothoracic TR 1.84–2.05 (1.96, 
<emphasis box="[893,906,1136,1159]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3), mesothoracic TR 2.05–2.22 (2.12, 
<emphasis box="[401,414,1168,1191]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3), metathoracic TR 1.90–2.15 (2.03, 
<emphasis box="[881,894,1168,1191]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3). Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1163,1167,1191]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
) length 2.75–3.03 (2.89, 
<emphasis box="[484,497,1200,1223]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3) mm, width 0.93–0.98 (0.95, 
<emphasis box="[896,909,1200,1223]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3) mm, costal ratio 0.75–0.79 (0.77, 
<emphasis box="[406,419,1232,1255]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3); membrane deeply infuscated; second radial cell 3.54–4.40 (4.00, 
<emphasis box="[283,296,1264,1287]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">n</emphasis>
= 3) × longer than first; cubital fork originating at level of base of r-m cross vein; macrotrichia on costa, R 
<subScript attach="right" box="[559,569,1305,1321]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[605,615,1305,1321]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">2</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[657,673,1305,1321]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">1,</subScript>
sparse on cells r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[864,874,1305,1321]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">3</subScript>
, m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[911,921,1305,1321]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">1</subScript>
. Halter pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,816,1606]" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
Abdomen. Dark brown, with dense, large, setae. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[931,1079,1327,1351]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Figure 3E, F</figureCitation>
): tergite 9 extending slightly beyond apex of gonocoxite, posterior margin bilobate, each lobe with slender lateral membranous extension; sternite 9 1.47× broader than long, with posteromedian hyaline projection. Gonocoxite 1.30× longer than greatest breadth, inner margin with mesal pointed tubercle; gonostylus stout, heavily sclerotized, nearly straight, tip rounded. Parameres subparallel, basal apodemes slender; stem rodshaped, apical 1/3 slightly broader, tip truncate. Aedeagus 0.50× length of basal breadth, composed of two convergent, slightly sclerotized sclerites, each slender, sinuous with distal portion curved, tip pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,936,1667,1691]" box="[212,936,1667,1691]" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">
<heading box="[212,936,1667,1691]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="167" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,299,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="167">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male, with the following notable differences:
</heading>
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="168" startId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" targetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,1476,1586]" pageId="13" pageNumber="168">
Figure 3. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ingram and Macfie" authorityName="Ingram and Macfie" authorityYear="1931" box="[251,704,1476,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Stilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta" subGenus="Acanthohelea">
<emphasis box="[251,359,1476,1497]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="168">Stilobezzia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[377,402,1476,1497]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="168">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[419,487,1476,1497]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="168">hirsuta</emphasis>
Ingram and Macfie
</taxonomicName>
: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,168,670]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[332,452,168,192]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">Figure 3G</figureCitation>
). Antennal flagellum dark brown, bases slightly paler; antennal ratio 1.48–1.64 (1.56, 
<emphasis box="[460,473,201,224]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3); palpal ratio 3.57–4.14 (3.85, 
<emphasis box="[872,885,201,224]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3). Mandible with 7–8 coarse teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,168,670]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
Thorax. Scutellum with 10–12 large, 8–10 thinner setae. Legs pale brown; tarsomere 1 of mid leg with basal spine; prothoracic TR 1.87–2.06 (1.92, 
<emphasis box="[1083,1096,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3), mesothoracic TR 1.94–2.06 (2.02, 
<emphasis box="[609,622,329,352]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3), metathoracic TR 1.94–2.21 (2.06, 
<emphasis box="[1092,1105,329,352]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3). Wing (
<figureCitation box="[291,410,359,383]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">Figure 3H</figureCitation>
) length 2.38–2.80 (2.60, 
<emphasis box="[696,709,361,384]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) mm, width 0.93–1.07 (1.02, 
<emphasis box="[1100,1113,361,384]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) mm, costal ratio 0.75–0.80 (0.78, 
<emphasis box="[595,608,392,415]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3); second radial cell 3.00–3.25 (3.12, 
<emphasis box="[1075,1088,392,415]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) × longer than first; cubital fork originating at level of base of r-m cross vein; macrotrichia on costa, R 
<subScript attach="right" box="[425,435,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[471,481,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">2</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="right" box="[518,528,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">3</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[570,585,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">1,</subScript>
M 
<subScript attach="right" box="[621,631,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">2</subScript>
, Cua 
<subScript attach="left" box="[693,703,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">2</subScript>
, abundant on cells r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[939,949,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">3</subScript>
, m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[987,997,466,482]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">1</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,168,670]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
Abdomen. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[511,620,487,511]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="13.[144,211,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[144,1092,168,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[144,1104,168,1444]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 3. Stilobezzia (A.) hirsuta Ingram and Macfie: (A–F) male; (A) head; (B) wing; (C) thorax detail (lateral view); (D) thorax (lateral view); (E) abdomen; (F) genitalia (ventral view), detail of posteromedian projection of sternite 9, parameres removed and detail of posterior margin of tergite 9. (G–I) female; (G) head; (H) wing; (I) genitalia. Scale bars 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4002631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4002631/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">Figure 3I</figureCitation>
) sternite 8 heavily sclerotized, anterior margin straight, lateral margins subparallel, posteromedian excavation shallow, V-shaped; sternite 10 with 5 pairs of setae; cerci rounded; two globular spermathecae with very short, narrow necks, measuring 9.60–11.40 (10.80, 
<emphasis box="[789,802,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) by 8.10–11.40 (9.70, 
<emphasis box="[1102,1115,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) µm and 8.50–9.60 (9.20, 
<emphasis box="[505,518,616,639]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) by 7.00–9.20 (7.90, 
<emphasis box="[824,837,616,639]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">n</emphasis>
= 3) µm; plus a small third rudimentary spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
