<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,1258,1417]" box="[212,328,1258,1281]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
<heading box="[212,328,1258,1281]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="169" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,328,1258,1281]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">Discussion</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,1258,1417]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
This species greatly resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ingram &amp; Macfie" authorityYear="1931" box="[554,633,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Stilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rava">
<emphasis box="[554,570,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[585,633,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">rava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ingram &amp; Macfie" authorityYear="1931" box="[868,947,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Stilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rava">
<emphasis box="[868,884,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[899,947,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">rava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ by the tergite 9 that does not extend beyond the apex of the gonocoxites and its posterior margin is nearly straight. Females differ by the divergent lateral margins of the sternite 8 and by the pyriform spermathecae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,862,1484,1548]" box="[212,310,1484,1508]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
<heading box="[212,310,1484,1508]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="169" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,310,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,862,1484,1548]" box="[212,862,1524,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">
Several males have a paler gonostylus than the 
<typeStatus box="[755,857,1524,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="169">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
